Parliament, Monday, 19 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Communications will tomorrow (20 March 2018) be briefed by the Parliamentary Constitutional and Legal Services on the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (Icasa) council chairperson, Mr Rubben Mohlaloga. It will also be briefed by Icasa and the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) on their 2017/18 second quarter expenditure and performance reports. Committee Room V119, First Floor, Old Assembly Building, 10:00 Date: Tuesday, 20 March 2018 Time: 10:00 Venue: Committee Room V119, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COMMUNICATIONS, MR HUMPHREY MAXEGWANA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
